\section{\texorpdfstring{Paragraph
Numbers\hyperref[paragraph-numbers]{}}{Paragraph Numbers}}\label{paragraph-numbers}

\subsection{\texorpdfstring{Manual Paragraph
Numbers\hyperref[manual-paragraph-numbers]{}}{Manual Paragraph Numbers}}\label{manual-paragraph-numbers}

\pnum{2} An expression is \emph{potentially evaluated} unless it is an
unevaluated operand (7.2) or a subexpression thereof. The set of
\emph{potential results} of an expression \VERB|\NormalTok{e}| is
defined as follows:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  \pnum{(2.1)} If \VERB|\NormalTok{e}| is an
  \VERB|\NormalTok{\emph{id-expression}}| (7.5.4), the set contains only
  \VERB|\NormalTok{e}|.
\item
  \pnum{(2.2)} If \VERB|\NormalTok{e}| is a subscripting operation
  (7.6.1.1) with an array operand, the set contains the potential
  results of that operand.
\end{itemize}

\pnum{2} Explicitly pins the wording-local paragraph number to
\VERB|\DecValTok{2}|.

\pnum{(2.1)}
\VERB|\OperatorTok{[}\FloatTok{2.1}\OperatorTok{]\{.}\NormalTok{pnum}\OperatorTok{\}}|
explicitly pins the nested count.

\pnum{(2.2)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically continues
to \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{2.2}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{3} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically continues to
\VERB|\DecValTok{3}|.

\pnum{(3.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically starts
the nested count at \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{3.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(2.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[2.\#]\{.pnum\}}| resets the nested count
to \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{2.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{x} \VERB|\NormalTok{x}| doesn't contribute to automatic numbering.

\pnum{(x.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically starts the
nested count at
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\NormalTok{x}\FloatTok{.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(x.2)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically continues
to \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\NormalTok{x}\FloatTok{.2}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{x} \VERB|\NormalTok{x}| resets its own nested count.

\pnum{(x.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| automatically restarts
at \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\NormalTok{x}\FloatTok{.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(3.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.\#]\{.pnum\}}| returns to the numeric
path and continues to
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{3.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(3.x.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| starts a literal
nested path at
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{3.}\ErrorTok{x.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(3.x.2)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| continues the
literal nested path at
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{3.}\ErrorTok{x.2}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(3.2)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.\#]\{.pnum\}}| returns to the numeric
nested count at \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{3.2}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(4.2.5)} Explicitly pins a deeper numeric path.

\pnum{(4.x.1)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| starts a separate
literal nested path at
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{4.}\ErrorTok{x.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(4.x.2)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.x.\#]\{.pnum\}}| continues the
literal nested path at
\VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{4.}\ErrorTok{x.2}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\pnum{(4.3)} \VERB|\NormalTok{[\#.\#]\{.pnum\}}| returns to the numeric
nested count at \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{4.3}\OperatorTok{)}|.

\subsection{\texorpdfstring{Automatic Paragraph
Numbers\hyperref[automatic-paragraph-numbers]{}}{Automatic Paragraph Numbers}}\label{automatic-paragraph-numbers}

\pnum{1} \VERB|\NormalTok{\#.}| automatically starts at
\VERB|\DecValTok{1}|.

\pnum{2} Another \VERB|\NormalTok{\#.}| automatically continues to
\VERB|\DecValTok{2}|.

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \pnum{(2.1)} Nested bullet list also gets automatic numbering.
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{2.1}\OperatorTok{)}|.

  {[}\ldots{]}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \pnum{(2.5)} Example of skipping. Pin to \VERB|\NormalTok{5.}|, yields
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{2.5}\OperatorTok{)}|.
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \pnum{(2.6)} Continues to
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{(}\FloatTok{2.6}\OperatorTok{)}|.

  \begin{itemize}
  \item
    \pnum{(2.6.1)} Nested nested bullet list should just work
    \VERB|\NormalTok{(2.6.1)}|.

    {[}\ldots{]}
  \end{itemize}

  \begin{itemize}
  \item
    \pnum{(2.6.9)} \VERB|\NormalTok{9.}| here will bring us to
    \VERB|\NormalTok{(2.6.9)}|.
  \end{itemize}

  \begin{itemize}
  \item
    \pnum{(2.6.x)} \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| here will be
    \VERB|\NormalTok{(2.6.x)}|.
  \item
    \pnum{(2.6.x)} Another \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| here will also be
    \VERB|\NormalTok{(2.6.x)}|.
  \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\pnum{3} \VERB|\NormalTok{\#.}| automatically continues to
\VERB|\DecValTok{3}|.

Also handle code blocks within a list item:

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\DataTypeTok{int}\NormalTok{ main}\OperatorTok{();}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\pnum{x} Use \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| to skip a paragraph number.

\pnum{x} Another \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| assigned \VERB|\NormalTok{x}|.

\pnum{4} \VERB|\NormalTok{\#.}| automatically continues to
\VERB|\DecValTok{4}|.

\pnum{5} Pin with \VERB|\NormalTok{17.}|.

{\color[HTML]{006e28}\pnum{x} \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| is mainly to skip
numbering in \VERB|\NormalTok{add}|.

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \pnum{(x.1)} Nested bullet within an \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}|. This will
  be (x.1).
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \pnum{(x.x)} Nested \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}| within an
  \VERB|\NormalTok{x)}|. This will be (x.x).
\end{itemize}

\pnum{x} Second added paragraph.}

{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\pnum{6} \VERB|\NormalTok{\#.}| here will be 18
after the skips.

\pnum{7} Skip and pin again, e.g.~\VERB|\NormalTok{24.}|.}

\pnum{8} Automatically continue to 25.

